help:
usage: analyze/pcap/termshark [-h] [-i] [-g] [-o OUTPUT] [-v] [-c COUNT]
                              [-t TIMEOUT] [-f FILTER] [-r REGEX] [-x XREGEX]

    Analyze a pcap file using termshark.
    

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -i, --iterate         iterate over input
  -g, --generate        generate each output
  -o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT
                        output to file
  -v, --verbose         print debug info
  -c COUNT, --count COUNT
                        number of packets to read (all)
  -t TIMEOUT, --timeout TIMEOUT
                        number of seconds to read (infinite)
  -f FILTER, --filter FILTER
                        BPF filter to apply
  -r REGEX, --regex REGEX
                        expression(s) to qualify packet (AND)
  -x XREGEX, --xregex XREGEX
                        expression(s) to disqualify packet (OR)

usage: launch/elasticsearch [-h] [-i] [-g] [-o OUTPUT] [-v]
                            [--interface INTERFACE] [-p PORT]

    Launch Elasticsearch, a powerful open source search and
    analytics engine that makes data easy to explore.
    

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -i, --iterate         iterate over input
  -g, --generate        generate each output
  -o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT
                        output to file
  -v, --verbose         print debug info
  --interface INTERFACE
                        interface to listen on
  -p PORT, --port PORT  port to listen on

usage: launch/kibana [-h] [-i] [-g] [-o OUTPUT] [-v] [--interface INTERFACE]
                     [-p PORT] -e ELASTIC_URL

    Visualize Elasticsearch data with Kibana.
    

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -i, --iterate         iterate over input
  -g, --generate        generate each output
  -o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT
                        output to file
  -v, --verbose         print debug info
  --interface INTERFACE
                        interface to listen on
  -p PORT, --port PORT  port to listen on
  -e ELASTIC_URL, --elastic-url ELASTIC_URL
                        elasticsearch url to connect to
